\b Methods for download and upload:\

\b0 1). Download file from web or from the local disk\

\b public void Download(string url, bool isAutoSave, bool fromDisk)\

\b0 url : url of the file on the web\
isAutoSave : if true, then file will be downloaded and save to disk on a configured path.\
fromDisk : Download from local disk or from web\
\
2). Upload data as a byte array on the web server\

\b private void Upload(string url, string folderPath, string fileName, byte[] bytes)\

\b0 url : url of the file on the web\
folderPath : Name of the folder/directory where you want to save your file on the server\
fileName : Name of the file\
bytes : Byte array to be uploaded\
\
3). Upload file from the given path\

\b public void UploadFile(string webUrl , string folderPath, string filePath)\

\b0 webUrl : url of the file on the web\
folderPath : Name of the folder/directory where you want to save your file on the server\
filePath : Path of the file on the disk\
Note : if you pass \'93My Uploaded Files\'94 as folderPath, then \'93My Uploaded Files\'94 directory will be created if its not there in root folder. You can also pass \'93Uploads/My Files\'94 as folderPath if you want a sub directory \'93My Files\'94 in \'93Upload\'94 directory.\
